window.bookSummaryJSON = "With her infant son clutched to her breast, Maggie Stanley flees for her life. She has abandoned everything else to escape her abusive family. Ragged and hung-over, Rafe Kendricks is also on the run, trying to erase memories of the accident that killed his wife and child. Maggie and Rafe meet in a moment of mutual need, but soon the young woman will find that Rafe is not who he appears to be. <i>Baby Love</i> is a moving story of the heart and its capacity for love and trust. <p> With Suzanne Toren's lyrical narration, each scene, whether tender or violent, takes on added emotional depth.</p> <p> Catherine Anderson has published 16 romance novels and is a <i>New York Times</i> best-selling author. Her works, including <i>Cherish</i>, have quickened the pulses of readers around the world.</p>"; 
